butter /ˈbʌtə/

(buttering,buttered,butters) 

1. N-MASS Butter is a soft yellow substance made from cream. You spread it on bread or use it in cooking. 黄油 

例： ...bread and butter. ...面包和黄油。 

2. V-T If you butter something such as bread or toast, you spread butter on it. 涂黄油 

例： She spread pieces of bread on the counter and began buttering them. 她放了几片面包在柜台上，开始给它们涂黄油。

